The paper discusses semantic parsing, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) that deals with mapping natural language to executable representations. This falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques to learn execution models for arbitrary language, which falls under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of distributional statistics, which is a common technique in information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper discusses the use of formal knowledge bases, which falls under the category of databases (cs.DB).
